==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superphosphate
<hw>Su`per*phos"phate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An acid phosphate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Superphosphate of lime</b></col> <fld>(Com. Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a fertilizer obtained by trating bone dust, bone black, or phosphorite with sulphuric acid, whereby the insoluble neutral calcium phosphate, <chform>Ca3(PO4)2</chform>, is changed to the primary or acid calcium phosphate <chform>Ca(H2PO4)2</chform>, which is soluble and therefore available for the soil.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superphysical</ent>⟦br⟧
